{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/lms","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"f8aaa93c-e036-5f36-b2f3-d61e0a6f91a6","html":"<p>This blog walks you through how to install and setting up <code class=\"language-text\">PupilFirst</code> from scratch</p>\n<h2 id=\"prerequisites\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#prerequisites\" aria-label=\"prerequisites permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Prerequisites</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>I assume you have installed git in your system </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">sudo apt install git-all  # To install git</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>Running a Linux Machine (This installation tested on Ubuntu 20 LTS)</li>\n<li>Make sure you have sufficient storage (around 20 GB free)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"dependencies\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#dependencies\" aria-label=\"dependencies permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Dependencies</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">sudo apt-get install imagemagick postgresql postgresql-contrib autoconf libtool nginx</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"clone-check-out-the-llvm-source-from-git-repository\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#clone-check-out-the-llvm-source-from-git-repository\" aria-label=\"clone check out the llvm source from git repository permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Clone (Check out) the llvm source from git repository</h2>\n<p>We first need to clone the repository. To save space, we do a <code class=\"language-text\">shallow</code> clone. If you want the complete source code, go check this link <a href=\"https://llvm.org/docs/GettingStarted.html#getting-the-source-code-and-building-llvm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Getting the source code and building LLVM</a>\nDoing this will also pull llvm subprojects such as Clang and others. </p>\n<h3 id=\"create-a-directory-and-clone\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#create-a-directory-and-clone\" aria-label=\"create a directory and clone permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Create a directory and clone</h3>\n<p> Create a new directory in your home folder</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">mkdir llvm\ncd llvm\ngit clone --depth 1 https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project.git</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"configure-and-build-llvm-and-clang\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#configure-and-build-llvm-and-clang\" aria-label=\"configure and build llvm and clang permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Configure and build LLVM and Clang</h2>\n<p> Once you have clone successfully, you can now execute the following commands in your terminal. </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">cd llvm-project\nmkdir build\ncd build\ncmake -G Ninja ../llvm</code></pre></div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Note that -G Ninja is a build system generator; you can choose others as well. Check the official documentation <sup id=\"fnref-1\"><a href=\"#fn-1\" class=\"footnote-ref\">1</a></sup> if you would like to build <code class=\"language-text\">llvm</code> other than <code class=\"language-text\">Ninja</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>If you haven’t installed <code class=\"language-text\">cmake</code>, go ahead and install it</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">sudo apt install cmake</code></pre></div>\n<p>Once done, run. </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\"> cmake -G Ninja ../llvm</code></pre></div>\n<p>If you haven’t installed <code class=\"language-text\">Ninja,</code> you will get errors as follows:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">Error: CMake was unable to find a build program corresponding to &quot;Ninja&quot;. \n\nCMAKE_MAKE_PROGRAM is not set. You probably need to select a different build tool. CMake \n\nError: CMAKE_C_COMPILER not set, after EnableLanguage CMake Error: CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER not \n\nset, after EnableLanguage CMake Error: CMAKE_ASM_COMPILER not set, after EnableLanguage -- Configuring incomplete, errors occurred!</code></pre></div>\n<h4 id=\"install-ninja\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#install-ninja\" aria-label=\"install ninja permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Install Ninja</h4>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">sudo apt-get install -y ninja-build</code></pre></div>\n<p>Once done, run the following command to generate the <code class=\"language-text\">build files.</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\"> cmake -G Ninja ../llvm</code></pre></div>\n<h4 id=\"building-llvm-and-clang\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#building-llvm-and-clang\" aria-label=\"building llvm and clang permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Building llvm and clang</h4>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">cmake --build  .</code></pre></div>\n<p>This might takes hours, depending on your machine. </p>\n<p>It took <code class=\"language-text\">1 hr (approx)</code> in my machine  (Intel Xeon, 32GB Ram). </p>\n<p>I also encountered an error in linking, error similar to the following </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">FAILED: lib/libLTO.so.13git</code></pre></div>\n<p> Do the following <sup id=\"fnref-2\"><a href=\"#fn-2\" class=\"footnote-ref\">2</a></sup></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">cmake -G Ninja -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -DLLVM_PARALLEL_LINK_JOBS=1 ../llvm\ncmake --build .</code></pre></div>\n<p> This error happens likely that you’re running out of memory <sup id=\"fnref-2\"><a href=\"#fn-2\" class=\"footnote-ref\">2</a></sup>.</p>\n<div class=\"footnotes\">\n<hr>\n<ol>\n<li id=\"fn-1\">\n<p><a href=\"https://llvm.org/docs/GettingStarted.html#getting-the-source-code-and-building-llvm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://llvm.org/docs/GettingStarted.html#getting-the-source-code-and-building-llvm</a></p>\n<a href=\"#fnref-1\" class=\"footnote-backref\">↩</a>\n</li>\n<li id=\"fn-2\">\n<p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/65633304/not-able-to-build-llvm-from-its-source-code\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://stackoverflow.com/questions/65633304/not-able-to-build-llvm-from-its-source-code</a></p>\n<a href=\"#fnref-2\" class=\"footnote-backref\">↩</a>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</div>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/lms","tagSlugs":["/tag/lms/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2021-05-21T22:40:32.169Z","description":"Installing and Setting up PupilFirst ","tags":["lms"],"title":"Installing and Setting up PupilFirst","socialImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/lms"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","401334301","825871152"]}